I think, Ian is in error here.

My remark was based on authoritative sources, viz. "The REXX Language"
by M. F. Cowlishaw, ISBN 0-13-780685-X, "The REXX Language" 2nd edition,
ISBN 0-13-780651-5, and the minutes of the ANSI X3J18 REXX Standards
Committee. All of these indicate, without any restriction, that question,
and exclamation, marks may be used to form the names of variables (cf.
quotes below), while some other characters were disallowed by the 2nd
edition of "The REXX Language". The X3J18 Committee has followed this
approach.  What X3J18 reserved for further use was a subset of the
constant symbols (which anyway cannot be used to name variables), cf.
quote below.

If indeed Mike Cowlishaw has informed anybody otherwise, I would like
to see evidence posted in this forum.


As this thread has started from a wrong assumption about the characters
possibly used for the Not sign, in REXX, I'm also going to append a quote
from X3J18 on this issue.


